  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nOther (please describe)\r\n\r\n### Describe the feature you would like\r\n\r\n[Fig](https://fig.io) is terminal add - on that increases developer productivity by providing auto completion for over 400 popular CLIs and IDEs (VsCode , JetBrains, Hyper)\r\n\r\nFig is also easily extensible to cover most CLIs written in popular CLI frameworks. \r\n\r\nIn addition to the above , its quick to set up and maintain , which minimizes its operational burden, as publishing new figma specs can be automated on with the CI and pushed out to the figma store/ \r\n\r\n## Limitations\r\n- Only available on Mac at the moment.  (Linux / Windows coming soon).\r\n\r\n## Tasks\r\n- [x] Add spec generation code to cast, forge and anvil\r\n- [ ] Update CI to automatically update Fig repo when new releases of foundry are available\r\n\r\n### Additional context\r\n\r\nMotivated by this discussion : https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/discussions/2729",
